questionResults.questionText: Tell me about the Adidas GMR smart insole
questionResults.response:
Denys Honcharenko worked on the Adidas GMR smart insole project as a Lead Software Engineer at EPAM Systems from February 2020 to June 2020. The Adidas GMR was a smart insole system developed in collaboration between Adidas, Google (Jacquard technology), and EA Sports. It tracked real-world soccer performance and converted it into rewards in EA SPORTS FIFA Mobile game. The product featured shot power measurement, distance & speed tracking, kick detection, FIFA Mobile integration, global leaderboards, and universal fit compatibility with any footwear.

Denys and his team successfully delivered the project on time, despite it being a failing project initially. They also created a BLE emulator that increased QA efficiency by 10 times.
